executing the build and evaluating
<a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/build-checks/">build checks</a>.</p><p>For Dockerfiles, the available methods are:</p><div class="overflow-x-auto"><table><thead class="bg-gray-light-100 dark:bg-gray-dark-200"><tr><th class="p-2">Command</th><th class="p-2">Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="p-2"><code>build</code> (default)</td><td class="p-2">Execute the build and evaluate build checks for the current build target.</td></tr><tr><td class="p-2"><code>check</code></td><td class="p-2">Evaluate build checks for the either the entire Dockerfile or the selected target, without executing a build.</td></tr><tr><td class="p-2"><code>outline</code></td><td class="p-2">Show the build arguments that you can set for a target, and their default values.</td></tr><tr><td class="p-2"><code>targets</code></td><td class="p-2">List all the build targets in the Dockerfile.</td></tr><tr><td class="p-2"><code>subrequests.describe</code></td><td class="p-2">List all the frontend methods that the current frontend supports.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Note that other frontends may implement these or other methods.
