<code>docker</code>
<a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/build/builders/drivers/">build driver</a>, is a container
image exported to the local image store. The <code>--output</code> flag makes this step
configurable allows export of results directly to the client's filesystem, an
OCI image tarball, a registry, and more.</p><p>Buildx with <code>docker</code> driver only supports the local, tarball, and image
<a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/build/exporters/">exporters</a>. The <code>docker-container</code>
driver supports all exporters.</p><p>If you only specify a filepath as the argument to <code>--output</code>, Buildx uses the
local exporter. If the value is <code>-</code>, Buildx uses the <code>tar</code> exporter and writes
the output to stdout.</p><div data-pagefind-ignore="" class="scroll-mt-20" x-data="" x-ref="root"><div class="group relative"><button x-data="{ code: '', copying: false }" class="absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600" title="copy" @click="window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$>]\s+/gm, ''));
