A secret can be mounted into the build using a <code>RUN --mount=type=secret</code> mount in the
<a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/dockerfile/#run---mounttypesecret">Dockerfile</a>.
For more information about how to use build secrets, see
<a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/build/building/secrets/">Build secrets</a>.</p><p>Supported types are:</p><ul><li><a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/cli/docker/buildx/build/#typefile"><code>type=file</code></a></li><li><a class="link" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/cli/docker/buildx/build/#typeenv"><code>type=env</code></a></li></ul><p>Buildx attempts to detect the <code>type</code> automatically if unset. If an environment
