<code>type</code> is not set, then Buildx falls back to <code>type=file</code>.</p><h4 class="scroll-mt-20" id="typefile"><a class="text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/cli/docker/buildx/build/#typefile"><code>type=file</code></a></h4><p>Source a build secret from a file.</p><h5 class="scroll-mt-20" id="typefile-synopsis"><a class="text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline" href="https://docs.docker.com/reference/cli/docker/buildx/build/#typefile-synopsis"><code>type=file</code> synopsis</a></h5><div data-pagefind-ignore="" class="scroll-mt-20" x-data="" x-ref="root"><div class="group relative"><button x-data="{ code: 'JCBkb2NrZXIgYnVpbGR4IGJ1aWxkIC0tc2VjcmV0IFt0eXBlPWZpbGUsXWlkPTxJRD5bLHNyYz08RklMRVBBVEg+XSAu', copying: false }" class="absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600" title="copy" @click="window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$>]\s+/gm, ''));
